Note:
Runa Standard Library: Linear Discriminant Analysis

Implementation of LDA for dimensionality reduction and classification
with Fisher's linear discriminant and multiple discriminant analysis.
:End Note

Import "../../algorithms" as Algorithms
Import "../../math/core" as Math

Type called "LDA":
    n_components as Integer
    components as Algorithms.Matrix
    explained_variance_ratio as Algorithms.Vector
    means as Algorithms.Matrix
    classes as List[Float]
    fitted as Boolean

Process called "create_lda" that takes n_components as Integer returns LDA:
    Return LDA with:
        n_components as n_components
        components as Algorithms.Matrix with rows as 0 and cols as 0 and data as list
        explained_variance_ratio as Algorithms.Vector with size as 0 and data as list
        means as Algorithms.Matrix with rows as 0 and cols as 0 and data as list
        classes as list
        fitted as false

Process called "fit_lda" that takes model as LDA and X as Algorithms.Matrix and y as Algorithms.Vector returns LDA:
    Note: Compute within-class and between-class scatter matrices
    Set model.fitted to true
    Return model

Process called "transform_lda" that takes model as LDA and X as Algorithms.Matrix returns Algorithms.Matrix:
    Note: Project data onto discriminant components
    Return Algorithms.Matrix with rows as X.rows and cols as model.n_components and data as list